rComments: By far the most caring and professional proff I've ever had, and I am a fifth year student who's taken too many psych courses in two U of T campus. He does test on details. But, he explains everything well during lecture, and is more than willing to re-explain and clarify materials.

Prof. Ryan is one of my favourite professors Ive ever had. He really cares for the success of his students, more than any prof I know. His lectures are very enjoyable and I always looked forward to them. Tests are fair but pretty long. Definitely planning on taking other courses with him!
Professor R. is really kind and cares about his students' success, he is willing to stay in office hours for as long as you need and he entertains all types of questions.

Had him for health psych as well and he is one of my favorite profs. A little heavier on assignments compared to other psych classes. I wish the assignments were worth more of the grade, midterm/final are still 30-40% ish. Need to know details to do well on tests, knowing the general concept is not enough. Great prof.
really inspiring person. He puts a lot more thought, time, and effort into his courses than most other profs. a real gem.

I had Will for two classes now (PSY333&PSY336). He is genuinely the most amazing professor I ever had. The stuff I learn in his class really changed my life. I have adopted great habits and for the first time in over 10 years I can say I have hope and more happiness for the future. This isnt just another psychology class. Thank you Will.

I really enjoyed the variety of topics. The Professor was accommodating to student needs and was always available. While I enjoyed the variety of coursework, I didn't find the weighting of the assignments vs. exams appropriate for the effort. The mid-term & final exam  60% with the remaining 40% divided between SO MANY assignments. Exam was tough.

One of the best profs I've ever had. Had no interest in health psychology beforehand but he made the content extremely easy to understand and lectures were very interesting! Very accessible outside of class and genuinely wants students to succeed. Got to do assignments based on what interested us and brought out our creative sides. Really funny too

The professor is very approachable and is always happy to answer questions. He is clear in his answers. His tests and exams are highly based on the lectures, though readings will help you to do better so it's important to take notes since not all of it is on the slides. He genuinely cares about his students and he wants you to do well.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read', 'Participation matters']
